      "body": "<p class=\"question\"></p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "body": "\n        Doprowadź wyrażenie do najprostszej postaci:\n        <div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n            \\[\n            14!\\cdot 30-15!\n            \\]\n        </div>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "spoiler",
      "label": "rozwiązanie",
      "body": "\n\n<div class=\"switch_steps\">\n<div class=\"switch_step\">\n<div class=\"switch_line\">\n                    Na początek zauważmy, że \\(30=15\\cdot 2\\), więc \\(14!\\cdot 30=14!\\cdot 15\\cdot 2=\\)\n                    <div class=\"switch_value\">&gt;&gt; wybierz &gt;&gt;</div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\\(28!\\cdot 30\\)</div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\\(15!\\cdot 2\\)</div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\\(420\\)</div>\n<div class=\"switch_show_next ks_button\">zatwierdź</div>.\n                </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"switch_step hidden\">\n<p>\n                    Aby uprościć to wyrażenie, wyłączymy największy wspólny czynnik przed nawias.\n                </p>\n<div class=\"switch_line\">\n                    Największym wspólnym czynnikiem liczb \\(15!\\cdot 2\\) oraz \\(15!\\) jest \n                    <div class=\"switch_value\">&gt;&gt; wybierz &gt;&gt;</div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\\(15!\\)</div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\\(14!\\)</div>\n<div class=\"switch_show_next ks_button\">zatwierdź</div>.\n                </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"switch_step hidden\">\n<div class=\"switch_line\">\n                    I dlatego \\(15!\\cdot 2-15!=\\)\n                    <div class=\"switch_value\">&gt;&gt; wybierz &gt;&gt;</div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\\(15!(2-0)\\)</div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\\(15!(2-1)\\)</div>\n<div class=\"switch_show_next ks_button\">zatwierdź</div>.\n                </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"switch_step hidden\">\n                Tak więc\n                <div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n                    \\[\n                    \\begin{align}\n                    14!\\cdot 30-15!&amp;=15!\\cdot 2-15!=\\\\\n                    &amp;=15!(2-1)=\\\\\n                    &amp;=15!\n                    \\end{align}\n                    \\]\n                </div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "body": "<p class=\"question\"></p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "body": "\n        Doprowadź wyrażenie do najprostszej postaci:\n        <div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n            \\[\n            16!\\cdot 170+17!\\cdot 8\n            \\]\n        </div>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "spoiler",
      "label": "rozwiązanie",
      "body": "\n\n<div class=\"switch_steps\">\n<div class=\"switch_step\">\n<div class=\"switch_line\">\n                    Najpierw zauważmy, że \\(16!\\cdot 170=16!\\cdot 17\\cdot 10=\\)\n                    <div class=\"switch_value\">&gt;&gt; wybierz &gt;&gt;</div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\\(170!\\)</div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\\(17!\\cdot 10\\)</div>\n<div class=\"switch_show_next ks_button\">zatwierdź</div>.\n                </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"switch_step hidden\">\n<p>\n                    Teraz możemy wyłączyć czynnik \\(17!\\) przed nawias.\n                </p>\n<div class=\"switch_line\">\n                    \\(17!\\cdot 10+17!\\cdot 8=\\)\n                    <div class=\"switch_value\">&gt;&gt; wybierz &gt;&gt;</div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\\(17!(10+8)\\)</div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\\(17!(10-8)\\)</div>\n<div class=\"switch_show_next ks_button\">zatwierdź</div>.\n                </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"switch_step hidden\">\n<div class=\"switch_line\">\n                    A liczba \\(17!(10+8)\\) może być dalej przekształcona: \\(17!(10+8)=17!\\cdot 18=\\)\n                    <div class=\"switch_value\">&gt;&gt; wybierz &gt;&gt;</div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\\(18!\\)</div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\\(17!\\cdot 18!\\)</div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\\(17\\cdot 18\\)</div>\n<div class=\"switch_show_next ks_button\">zatwierdź</div>.\n                </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"switch_step hidden\">\n                Czyli:\n                <div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n                    \\[\n                    \\begin{align}\n                    16!\\cdot 170+17!\\cdot 8&amp;=17!\\cdot 10+17!\\cdot 8=\\\\\n                    &amp;=17!(10+8)=\\\\\n                    &amp;=17!\\cdot 18=\\\\\n                    &amp;=18!\n                    \\end{align}\n                    \\]\n                </div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "body": "<p class=\"question\"></p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "body": "\n        Oblicz:\n        <div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n            \\[\n            \\frac{9!}{6!\\cdot 3!}\n            \\]\n        </div>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "spoiler",
      "label": "rozwiązanie",
      "body": "\n\n<div class=\"switch_steps\">\n<div class=\"switch_step\">\n<div class=\"switch_line\">\n                    Najpierw skrócmy \\(9!\\) z \\(6!\\), korzystając z tego, że \\(\\frac{9!}{6!}=\\)\n                    <div class=\"switch_value\">&gt;&gt; wybierz &gt;&gt;</div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\\(6\\cdot 7\\cdot 8\\cdot 9\\)</div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\\(7\\cdot 8\\cdot 9\\)</div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\\(7\\cdot 9\\)</div>\n<div class=\"switch_show_next ks_button\">zatwierdź</div>.\n                </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"switch_step hidden\">\n                Czyli\n                <div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n                    \\[\n                    \\begin{align}\n                    \\frac{9!}{6!\\cdot 3!}&amp;=\\frac{7\\cdot 8\\cdot 9}{3!}=\\\\\n                    &amp;=\\frac{7\\cdot 8\\cdot 9}{1\\cdot 2\\cdot 3}\n                    \\end{align}\n                    \\]\n                </div>\n<div class=\"switch_line\">\n                    I teraz wystarczy skrócić licznik z mianownikiem, a dokładniej \\(8\\) z \\(2\\) oraz \\(9\\) z \\(3\\), by dostać:\n                    <div class=\"switch_value\">&gt;&gt; wybierz &gt;&gt;</div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\\(7\\cdot 4\\cdot 3\\)</div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\\(7\\cdot 4\\cdot 6\\)</div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\\(7\\cdot 6\\cdot 3\\)</div>\n<div class=\"switch_show_next ks_button\">zatwierdź</div>.\n                </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"switch_step hidden\">\n<div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n                    \\[\n                    \\begin{align}\n                    \\frac{9!}{6!\\cdot 3!}&amp;=\\frac{7\\cdot 8\\cdot 9}{3!}=\\\\\n                    &amp;=\\frac{7\\cdot 8\\cdot 9}{1\\cdot 2\\cdot 3}=\\\\\n                    &amp;=\\frac{7\\cdot 4\\cdot 3}{1\\cdot 1\\cdot 1}=\\\\\n                    &amp;=7\\cdot 4\\cdot 3=\\\\\n                    &amp;=84\n                    \\end{align}\n                    \\]\n                </div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"
    }
